-----------------------------------------------------------
This Diary is filed daily. ** Indicates new events

FRIDAY, SEPTEMBER 15
MOSCOW - Central Bank of Russia interest rate decision – 1030 GMT.
SATURDAY, SEPTEMBER 16
YANGON - Hong Kong Chief Executive Carrie Lam delivers speech at event the World Chinese
Entrepreneurs Convention in Yangon - 1130 GMT.
SINGAPORE - Indonesia Finance Minister Mulyani Indrawati is speaker at the annual Singapore
Summit - 0045 GMT.
MONDAY, SEPTEMBER 18
** BANGKOK - Bank of Thailand holds a two-day symposium with opening speech by the governor
Veerathai Santiprabhob (to September 19).
TUESDAY, SEPTEMBER 19
HONG KONG - Hong Kong's last British governor, Chris Patten, to give speech in Hong Kong - 0430
GMT.
BUDAPEST - Hungarian Central Bank rate-setting meeting.
BUDAPEST - Hungarian Central Bank to discuss the final version of its inflation report.
WARSAW - National Bank of Poland monetary policy meeting (no interest rate announcement).
CAPE TOWN - South African Reserve Bank starts its three-day monetary policy committee meeting
(to September 21).
SYDNEY - Reserve Bank of Australia (RBA) will release the minutes of September monetary policy
meeting - 0130 GMT.
WEDNESDAY, SEPTEMBER 20
SYDNEY  - Reserve Bank of Australia Assistant Governor (Economic) Luci Ellis will give speech at
the Australian Business Economists (ABE) conference, Sydney - 0230 GMT.
JAKARTA - Indonesia Central Bank board of governors meeting (to September 22).
THURSDAY, SEPTEMBER 21
PERTH, Australia - Reserve Bank of Australia Governor Philip Lowe will give speech at the
American Chamber of Commerce in Australia Business Briefing, Perth - 0200 GMT.
MANILA - Philippines Central Bank monetary policy meeting.
ANKARA - Turkish central bank to release minutes of its September monetary policy meeting - 1100
GMT.

FRIDAY, SEPTEMBER 22
JAKARTA - Indonesia Central Bank board of governors meeting.

MONDAY, SEPTEMBER 25
SYDNEY  - Panel participation by Michele Bullock, Assistant Governor (Financial Stability) of
the Reserve Bank of Australia, at the "Where to from here?" - Briefing hosted by Lander & Rogers
and Westpac, Sydney – 2115 GMT.
ABUJA - Central Bank of Nigeria monetary policy meeting and interest rate announcement (to
September 26).

TUESDAY, SEPTEMBER 26

economic outlook and monetary policy before the Atlanta Press Club - 1630 GMT.
